Before running `gwctl create cluster` we will need to update a few of the config files:

1. Disable Loki:  
   1. [https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/configmap.yaml\#L36](https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/configmap.yaml#L36)  
   2. Loki is currently hamstrung by being unable to access s3 in the kind cluster, so we disable it to reduce memory pressure.  
2. Disable promtail:  
   1. [https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/configmap.yaml\#L80](https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/configmap.yaml#L80)  
   2. Since there is no place for prometheus logs to go, just disable this for now.  
3. Add the keycloak namespace \+ realm information:  
   1. [https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/ns-keycloak.yaml](https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/ns-keycloak.yaml)  
   2. [https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/kustomization.yaml\#L16](https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/kustomization.yaml#L16)  
   3. [https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/kustomization.yaml\#L6-L12](https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/kustomization.yaml#L6-L12)  
   4. There’s currently a circular dependency when trying to import the realm data and creating the keycloak namespace; we explicitly make the namespace first to fix this.  
4. **IF RUNNING ON MAC \+ DOCKER DESKTOP:** Create an external redis instance:  
   1. [https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/redis.yaml](https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/redis.yaml)  
   2. [https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/kustomization.yaml\#L17](https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/kustomization.yaml#L17)  
   3. [https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/configmap.yaml\#L184-L186](https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/configmap.yaml#L184-L186)  
   4. The redis image being used by big bang by default is alpine based. There’s an incompatibility between Docker Desktop and alpine in the way DD expects to do translations to arm instructions. We get around this by hosting our own redis instance and pointing argo at it.  
5. Update argo app name:  
   1. [https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/configmap.yaml\#L220-L221](https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/configmap.yaml#L220-L221)  
   2. The generated name uses caps, which argo doesn’t like. Also argo is looking for the `appName` field which is missing.  
6. **IF YOU HAVE LESS THAN 32 GB OF MEMORY:** Disable tempo:  
   1. [https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/configmap.yaml\#L31-L32](https://github.com/lykkin/gwtester/blob/main/localdev/configmap.yaml#L31-L32)  
   2. Tempo requests a ton of memory, and isn’t strictly necessary to get things configured. I am running with 24 gb for the cluster, so I decided to disable this for now.

After running `gwctl create cluster`:

1. Update the permissions on the worker node:  
   1. Run `docker exec -it edbpgai-worker /bin/bash` to shell into the worker node, then mkdir \-p /var/local-path-provisioner && chown 65534:65534 /var/local-path-provisioner.  
   2. There is a mismatch between the PV provisioner pod’s user settings and the default permissions for the worker node.
